title: Grateful Dead Live at Oakland Auditorium Arena on 1982-12-31
description:
Set 1

Cold Rain & Snow, CC Rider***, Cumberland Blues, Far From Me-> Cassidy, Ramble On Rose, Looks Like Rain, Day Job

Set 2

Sugar Magnolia-> Sugaree-> Women Are Smarter, Ship of Fools, Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Not Fade Away**-> Deal**-> Sunshine Daydream**

Set 3

Turn On Your Love Light*-> Tell Mama*, Baby What You Want Me To Do*, Hard To Handle*, Midnight Hour*, E: Brokedown Palace

*w/ Matt Kelly **w/ John Cippolina. Etta James and Tower of Power Horns played third set

reviews.review_text: Finally, the version I've been looking for Third set is great, to my ears. Since near the start of the archive I have been hoping this version of the show would get uploaded. Thank you. My reason being that this is the best mix, though not perfect, so you can hear everyone during the third set. The Dead sparkle and Jerry is on fire, all the other versions had the horns way too strong and drowning out all the best parts of the set! Please compare and I think most will agree! Peace

Yes, this is the way the tape sounded. It's grittier and funkier than the SBD capture. The SBD remasters here at LMA are brilliant and, perhaps, this version could stand some "work". Overall, however, I find this recording to be more pleasing to the ear.

Best way to spend a NYE My first New Year's Eve show, and it was a dandy!  Solid song selection, lots of energy through the entire show.  Third set had Etta James and Tower of Power horns along with the boys.  Check out Lovelight, and the midnight ring-in with Sugar Mag.
